# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# THREAT SURFACES — Git Commit Message Template
# fischer³ Education
#
# SETUP (run once per repository clone):
#   git config commit.template .gitmessage
#
# This template will open automatically when you run `git commit`
# without the -m flag. Fill in the sections below, then save and close.
# Lines beginning with # are ignored by Git.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------


# [TYPE](SCOPE): Short description — imperative mood, max 72 chars
# Example: feat(m01-u02): add level curves unit — notes, exercises, python lab


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# WHY (optional — explain motivation, not mechanics; leave blank if obvious)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------



# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REFERENCES (optional — issue numbers, related commits, cross-repo notes)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------



# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CHECKLIST — delete this section before committing, or leave as a reminder
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Content commits:
#   [ ] No [bracketed placeholder text] remaining in student-facing files
#   [ ] Learning objectives in notes match exercise and Python lab scope
#   [ ] Statistical bridge section present (notes + exercises)
#   [ ] LaTeX compiles without errors
#   [ ] Jupyter notebook runs clean (restart kernel + run all)
#   [ ] Refresher links in notes point to existing refresher folders
#   [ ] REFRESHER_INDEX.md updated if a new refresher was added
#   [ ] COURSE_GUIDE.md updated if module structure changed
#
# Preamble / infra commits:
#   [ ] latex-preamble.tex synced to threat-surfaces-solutions/assets/
#   [ ] Existing exercise and solution files tested with updated preamble
#
# Solutions commits (threat-surfaces-solutions repo only):
#   [ ] Grading notes present for each sub-problem
#   [ ] Solutions branch only — never merged to develop or main
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------


# ===========================================================================
# QUICK REFERENCE
# ===========================================================================
#
# TYPES
#   feat      New content: unit, refresher, exercise, notebook
#   fix       Correction: typo, wrong math, broken LaTeX or notebook
#   refactor  Restructure without content change: rename, reorder
#   infra     Tooling: GitHub Actions, templates, preamble, Moodle files
#   docs      Repo documentation: README, COURSE_GUIDE, BRANCHING_STRATEGY
#   wip       Work in progress: partial content, not ready for review
#
# SCOPES
#   m00               Module 00 (orientation)
#   m01 … m08         Modules 01–08
#   m02-u03           Specific module + unit
#   refresher         Any refresher module
#   solutions         Solutions repo content
#   template          Template file changes
#   preamble          LaTeX preamble changes
#   repo              Repository-wide changes
#
# EXAMPLES
#   feat(m01-u02): add level curves unit — notes, exercises, python lab
#   fix(m02-u03): correct chain rule application in worked example
#   feat(refresher): add basic-probability refresher with python lab
#   infra(preamble): add \posterior and \prior shorthand macros
#   docs(repo): update branching strategy — add preamble sync reminder
#   wip(m04-u02): hessian unit notes draft — exercises not yet started
#   fix(m03-u01): fix broken \Hess macro reference in exercise problem 3
# ===========================================================================